In terms of product segmentation, bleached fluff pulp and unbleached fluff pulp play pivotal roles in meeting the varied requirements of the market. Bleached fluff pulp, known for its superior quality and appearance, is commonly used in premium hygiene products that cater to a more quality-conscious consumer base. On the other hand, unbleached fluff pulp is favored for its cost-effectiveness and is often utilized in products where aesthetics are not a primary concern. The segmentation by application reveals that baby diapers hold the largest share in the market, followed by feminine hygiene products and adult incontinence products. The expanding availability and affordability of these products are driving their adoption across different demographic segments, thereby propelling the demand for fluff pulp.

